title: AHS third, SWR fourth at MPC CC Championships
text:
AHS third, SWR fourth at MPC CC Championships From staff reports 
PLEASANT GARDEN â€” The Asheboro and Southwestern Randolph High School cross country teams competed in the Mid-Piedmont Conference Cross Country Championships on Tuesday at Hagan-Stone Park. 
In the boys meet, Central Davidson placed first with 40 points, while Ledford was second (42), AHS third (102), SWR fourth (107), Western Guilford fifth (111) and Southern Guilford sixth (117). 
Individually for the Blue Comets, Austin Romero placed seventh overall in 17 minutes, 11.95 seconds, while Benjamin Carroll was 14th (18:06.77), Cameron Reid 23rd (18:59.67), Benjamin Clauser 27th (19:22.18) and Gerardo Joachin-Salmon 30th (19:38.15) to round out the top five. 
For the Cougars, Harrison McNeill placed third (16:40.36), Colin Kirkman 19th (18:42.74), Dylan Brown 20th (18:46.19), Dylan Singletary 32nd (19:53) and Cody Stultz 33rd (20:25.53). 
In the girls meet, CD was first (35), LHS second (52), WG third (74), SG fourth (92), SWR fifth (116) and AHS sixth (117). 
For the Cougars, Sarah Bidlespacher placed 17th (22:58.51), Micah Teague 18th (23:03.43), Sarah Teague 22nd (23:43.48), Kayla Cannon 26th (24:21.23) and Crista Wyrocki 33rd (25:13.85). 
Katy Cernava paced the Blue Comets, placing sixth overall (21:10.02), while Laura Koser finished 20th (23:30.78), Carter Hurley 25th (24:19.32), Madlin Muralles 32nd (25:12.91) and Allison Kauffman 34th (25:17.18). 
Romero and Cernava were both all-conference.
